<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8351&amp;p=86703#p86703</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8351&amp;p=86703#p86703"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NROM more than 40kB possible?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8351&amp;p=86703#p86703"><![CDATA[
Perhaps someone wants a hack to expand SMB1 to use UNROM, which is probably the simplest mapper if you just want to expand PRG. The biggest reasons I see to use SxROM instead of UNROM in a hack of SMB1 are for 1. rapid tile rotation with CHR ROM (e.g. spinning coins and ? blocks of SMB3) and 2. support for battery-backed PRG RAM if a game needs to save more than 32 bits (typical password capacity) of state across play sessions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Nov 23, 2011 6:35 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
